01:29.356 --> 01:34.359
         (wind howling)

02:17.738 --> 02:21.573
      (machinery clanking)

03:18.832 --> 03:20.532
         (woman hooting)

03:43.224 --> 03:46.558
        Hey boy, you that
         new Bison hand?

03:46.560 --> 03:47.726
          That's right.

03:47.728 --> 03:49.361
       Throw your shit in
      the back of the truck

03:49.363 --> 03:51.597
  and get your ass in here, we
  ain't got all day, come on.

03:51.599 --> 03:54.399
        (engine humming)

03:57.938 --> 03:59.004
         YY Pucketts.

04:01.008 --> 04:03.408
          Jim McNeely.
     [YY] Good to meet you.

04:05.813 --> 04:07.846
       How long you been
       working for Bison?

04:08.816 --> 04:09.948
   Shit, I've been with these

04:09.950 --> 04:11.516
 son-bitches since they started.

04:11.518 --> 04:13.952
    Funded by some old rich
  outfit up there outta Dallas

04:13.954 --> 04:15.954
      that don't know shit
      between goddamn air.

04:15.956 --> 04:17.623
    Hell them son a bitches
   I've been doing this still

04:17.625 --> 04:20.492
  for forever started out just
  like where you're starting.

04:20.494 --> 04:22.828
          You a weevil?
          [Jim] A what?

04:22.830 --> 04:25.430
     A boll-weevil, somebody
      who don't know shit.

04:25.432 --> 04:28.033
    That's a fella that ain't
 never been out to an oil patch.

04:28.035 --> 04:30.569
        [Jim] What do you
      reckon I'll be doing?

04:30.571 --> 04:32.337
     The first thing they're
       gonna do is they're

04:32.339 --> 04:34.039
  gonna have your ass out there
    goddamn diggin' ditches.

04:34.041 --> 04:35.474
 The next thing they gonna have

04:35.476 --> 04:36.908
      you do is buckin'up
        four inch pipe.

04:36.910 --> 04:38.777
      You get ready to get
      a dose of that shit.

04:38.779 --> 04:41.680
  I used to have two nuts, now
   both of 'em's up my belly.

04:43.884 --> 04:45.484
    I'll tell you right now,
         you'll need to

04:45.486 --> 04:46.752
 the break quarter and lay down.

04:46.753 --> 04:48.019
      I've seen guys didn't
       bathe for four days

04:48.022 --> 04:51.390
      they was so god-dang
     tired to get in there.

04:51.392 --> 04:53.825
        Thank you kindly
        for the ride, YY.

04:53.827 --> 04:55.761
 You can thank me in two weeks.

04:56.897 --> 04:59.898
     Do me a favor son, you
      tell that Cap Bruner

04:59.900 --> 05:03.335
      that YY Pucketts said
       to go fuck himself!

05:03.337 --> 05:04.403
           (laughing)

05:05.639 --> 05:06.571
            Oh, wait.

05:07.408 --> 05:08.373
            Hold up!

05:19.386 --> 05:20.419
            (knocks)

05:20.421 --> 05:22.421
             Hello.

05:22.423 --> 05:23.689
         Name's McNeely.

05:23.691 --> 05:25.757
    Hell, I know who you are.

05:25.759 --> 05:27.859
  Another favor from corporate.

05:29.730 --> 05:32.998
      Well I'm Dent Paxton,
       a friend to all men

05:33.000 --> 05:35.600
      so long as they don't
       ask anything of me.

05:35.602 --> 05:37.903
  Well I'm here, what do I do?

05:39.940 --> 05:41.640
    You can write, I presume?

05:47.381 --> 05:52.451
   You'll be in bunkhouse 1,
  bunk number 3, you got that?

05:53.520 --> 05:55.754
       Okay, now it's time
      for the free lecture.

05:55.756 --> 05:58.123
 Welcome to jolly Camp Dead Lake

05:58.125 --> 06:01.526
     of that great octopus,
     the Bison Oil Company.

06:01.528 --> 06:03.929
    Our sole purpose out here
     is to get that stinkin'

06:03.931 --> 06:06.531
      crude oil out of the
   ground and move it on down

06:06.533 --> 06:09.935
  the pipeline where it can be
 made into gasoline and dollars.

06:09.937 --> 06:13.605
   You'll be assigned to Cap
  Bruner's gang, God help you.

06:13.607 --> 06:16.608
   That's the connection gang,
 they do the oil field plumbing.

06:18.679 --> 06:20.779
     It don't sound so bad.

06:20.781 --> 06:23.415
      Buddy, I don't know
     what you've been doing

06:23.417 --> 06:26.084
 but whatever it is, I guarantee
   you it's better than this.

06:27.087 --> 06:30.489
        My advice to you
        is run like hell

06:30.491 --> 06:32.391
      because you'll either
      get run off in a week

06:32.393 --> 06:33.792
     or what's worse, you'll
      want to prove you're

06:33.794 --> 06:36.862
   a real tough character and
    get indentured for life.

06:36.864 --> 06:40.866
     Look, I ain't planning
       on gettin' run off

06:40.868 --> 06:44.936
  or becoming anybody's slave,
     I got plans of my own.

06:44.938 --> 06:47.139
        Well tough titty
        buddy, all hopes

06:47.141 --> 06:49.541
    and illusions are blasted
       to pieces out here.

06:49.543 --> 06:51.843
      Fair warning, go back
     to where you came from.

06:54.548 --> 06:56.148
  I got no place to go back to.

07:03.624 --> 07:07.659
     (relaxed violin music)

07:08.695 --> 07:10.762
      [Mazie] Jim McNeely,
     you better wait for me.

07:16.737 --> 07:19.704
