      spread out the line.

15:06.072 --> 15:08.006
   Cotton, you go with Scrap.

15:08.608 --> 15:10.275
             Buster,

15:10.277 --> 15:11.542
         you've got Jim.

15:22.155 --> 15:24.088
   You're going down, hotshot.

15:26.092 --> 15:29.360
     (anxious guitar tones)

15:35.502 --> 15:37.235
   Buster, can I talk to you?

15:44.611 --> 15:46.945
         Hot damn, that
       must've stung good.

15:49.449 --> 15:54.085
   Somehow you've got the idea
   that you need to break me.

15:54.087 --> 15:56.087
    You're gonna leave me be

15:56.089 --> 15:59.424
       from here on out,
       if you wanna live.

15:59.426 --> 16:04.495
   Don't think I'm gonna fight
   you fair. That I won't do.

16:06.199 --> 16:08.166
      And you got something
          to say to me,

16:08.168 --> 16:12.236
        you call me by my
      name. That's McNeely.

16:12.238 --> 16:15.373
      (guttural screaming)

16:22.082 --> 16:26.217
(mid tempo country guitar music)

16:41.267 --> 16:42.200
             Buster!

16:44.137 --> 16:46.070
    Shut up, you little rat.

