17:19.705 --> 17:21.138
          Howdy fellas.

17:22.308 --> 17:23.473
       You a boll-weevil?

17:23.476 --> 17:26.109
        Nah, I'm Clayton
        LeMane the Third.

17:27.747 --> 17:28.713
          Jim McNeely.

17:28.715 --> 17:30.615
   Damn good to meet ya, Jim.

17:30.617 --> 17:33.418
     Quit your fraternizing
  Stabber and get back to work.

17:34.487 --> 17:36.554
     Just like I was saying
      Mr. LeMane, there's

17:36.556 --> 17:38.723
  a lot to gettin' a days work
    out of a bunch of hands.

17:38.725 --> 17:40.591
   [Clayton] That sure is good
        to know Captain,

17:40.593 --> 17:42.593
  seeing as I'm a hand now too.

17:42.595 --> 17:44.062
         I'll be sure to
          put in a word

17:44.064 --> 17:46.130
      with my uncle for how
      amiable you've been.

17:49.069 --> 17:52.670
   (soft country guitar music)

17:54.274 --> 17:57.475
     Pay up son, them beers
     don't buy themselves.

18:00.380 --> 18:03.514
        You know why I'm
       so poor and measly?

18:03.516 --> 18:05.716
    Because my daddy was such
   a tight old son of a bitch,

18:05.718 --> 18:08.853
      he used to pay me 10
    cents not to have supper.

18:08.855 --> 18:10.421
        Then that bastard
         would charge me

18:10.423 --> 18:12.824
      a dime every morning
         for breakfast.

18:12.826 --> 18:14.826
  Meanest man there ever were.

18:14.828 --> 18:16.494
 It's a wonder I growed at all.

18:16.496 --> 18:18.096
   Pity you did, you old liar.

18:19.165 --> 18:21.566
     No sir, I ain't lying,
       that there I know.

