          [Lee] Hello.
          [Jim] Hello.

23:10.790 --> 23:14.558
 [Lee] It's a lovely afternoon.
[Jim] I hadn't noticed 'til now.

23:14.560 --> 23:17.928
   It must be the contrast, it
   was a real scorcher today.

23:17.930 --> 23:20.765
      Yeah it was, fella on
       the rig said he saw

23:20.767 --> 23:23.901
    a lizard crawl up a steam
     pipe just to cool off.

23:23.903 --> 23:25.136
             Really?

23:25.138 --> 23:27.571
     Fella said it, I can't
     say about the lizard.

23:28.875 --> 23:30.174
      I'm headed into town
      to get some candles.

23:30.176 --> 23:31.542
         My husband said
        the electricity's

23:31.544 --> 23:32.943
 going out for a while tonight?

23:32.945 --> 23:35.479
   [Jim] Yeah, they're cuttin'
      a new pumping station

23:35.481 --> 23:37.948
   into the power line but it
   shouldn't be out too long.

23:37.950 --> 23:40.084
       Is that why you're
      going into town too?

23:41.687 --> 23:43.087
          For candles?

23:43.089 --> 23:44.755
        And razorblades.

23:45.658 --> 23:46.757
       Do you want a ride?

23:49.762 --> 23:51.862
       Sure, thanks ma'am.

24:02.742 --> 24:05.109
      [Lee] I don't make a
     practice of picking up

24:05.110 --> 24:07.477
  strange men in the middle of
 the road but I recognized you.

24:07.480 --> 24:10.181
 [Jim] It's mighty kind of you.

24:10.183 --> 24:13.684
     (relaxed guitar music)

24:14.554 --> 24:16.720
   [Lee] Tell me Mr. McNeely,

24:16.722 --> 24:19.457
      how are you enjoying
     your stay in Dead Lake?

24:20.893 --> 24:21.959
      You can call me Jim.

24:21.961 --> 24:25.763
   But if I call you Jim, then
     you should call me Lee.

24:27.133 --> 24:30.534
  I'll call you Mrs. Montgomery
      like I'm supposed to.

24:31.637 --> 24:34.605
     I guess it wouldn't be
     proper, what a world.

24:35.942 --> 24:36.874
           It sure is.

24:38.511 --> 24:40.678
 Me being me and you being you.

24:40.680 --> 24:42.146
   I didn't mean it like that.

24:42.148 --> 24:46.550
     (pensive guitar music)

24:46.552 --> 24:47.818
       [Lee] Thanks Arnie.
        [Arnie] You bet.

24:47.820 --> 24:51.555
     Arnie, I'm gonna need
  another pack of razorblades.

24:55.027 --> 24:57.127
       Let me get a couple
         Schlitz to go.

24:59.165 --> 25:00.097
           Thank you.

25:02.668 --> 25:03.501
       Thanks for waiting.

25:03.503 --> 25:04.235
          [Lee] Mm hmm.

25:08.007 --> 25:10.875
     [Jim] How about a cold
     beer to ease us along?

25:11.944 --> 25:13.143
          [Lee] Are you
       offering me a beer?

25:14.614 --> 25:17.615
   No, I'm just trying to pay
    you for the ride is all.

25:22.522 --> 25:23.821
           Thank you.

25:24.657 --> 25:28.592
  (relaxed guitar, piano music)

25:36.035 --> 25:38.936
   I had almost forgotten how
    good a cold beer tastes.

25:41.073 --> 25:42.673
  If you had a million dollars,

25:42.675 --> 25:44.208
 you couldn't enjoy it any more.

25:47.547 --> 25:48.712
       I'll remember that.

25:50.216 --> 25:52.616
    [Jim] I'll tell you what,
      you can call me 'Hey'

25:53.920 --> 25:56.554
     and I'll call you 'Say'
   and then next time we meet,

25:56.556 --> 26:00.090
       you could say "Hey,
         how you doing?"

26:00.092 --> 26:03.827
     And I'll respond "Say,
       good to see you."

26:05.164 --> 26:06.096
          I like that.

26:11.938 --> 26:14.905
      [Lee] Thank you, you
      should get out here,

26:15.741 --> 26:17.074
          people talk.

26:20.012 --> 26:21.278
          Thanks again.

26:42.134 --> 26:45.936
   (tepid violin, piano music)

26:56.816 --> 27:00.784
          ¶ Da, da da ¶

27:00.786 --> 27:03.053
          ¶ Da da da ¶

27:05.291 --> 27:07.825
    [Jim] All right, turn it.

27:07.827 --> 27:08.792
            Come on.

27:08.794 --> 27:11.695
         ¶ I love you ¶

27:11.697 --> 27:14.064
  [Jim] One, two, three, snap!

27:14.066 --> 27:15.366
    [Cap] Come on, get it in.

27:15.368 --> 27:17.034
     [Jim] One, two, three.

27:17.036 --> 27:18.702
              Damn!

27:18.704 --> 27:20.137
        One, two, three.

27:20.139 --> 27:21.071
              Snap!

27:26.946 --> 27:32.016
    ¶ Of all the things that
   ever lived, I choose you ¶

27:34.320 --> 27:36.020
         ¶ To rue me, ¶

27:36.022 --> 27:41.091
      ¶ my Roooooosemary ¶

27:41.794 --> 27:43.694
          (shattering)

27:43.696 --> 27:45.696
        [Jim] All right
       boys, let's drink.

27:47.700 --> 27:49.266
  [Cap] Just a goddamn minute.

27:50.936 --> 27:52.136
 You ain't drawin' enough money

27:52.138 --> 27:54.438
        to be givin' the
      orders to these men.

27:58.978 --> 28:01.845
      A man don't live that
       makes enough money

28:01.847 --> 28:05.282
       to tell me when I
      can and won't drink.

28:17.997 --> 28:21.765
  [Cap] All right you scraps of
  nothing... get back to work!

28:29.408 --> 28:30.474
        [Lee] Thank you.

28:33.245 --> 28:34.945
          Razorblades?

28:35.815 --> 28:36.747
              Yeah.

28:38.250 --> 28:39.183
            Come on.

28:41.020 --> 28:42.986
 [Lee] Mazie's a beautiful name,
   you might still marry her.

28:42.988 --> 28:45.889
  I got pretty good instincts.
           [Jim] No.

28:45.891 --> 28:47.491
        All that's over
       and done with now.

28:48.961 --> 28:50.994
      Besides, she doesn't
    bother me anymore, only--

28:50.996 --> 28:51.962
        [Lee] Only what?

28:52.998 --> 28:54.965
    Say what you're thinking.

28:54.967 --> 28:58.235
     (relaxed violin music)

29:03.876 --> 29:06.510
   You should've just dropped
      me off at the gate.

29:08.948 --> 29:09.880
             I know.

29:22.795 --> 29:25.295
 You fill up my whole head, Lee.

29:25.297 --> 29:26.230
              What?

29:28.234 --> 29:29.299
           It's true.

29:31.237 --> 29:33.270
      Don't talk like that.

29:37.877 --> 29:39.409
    [Lee] What are you doing?

29:54.093 --> 29:55.025
           [Lee] Jim.

30:02.835 --> 30:04.401
     Oh God, Get off of me.

30:08.107 --> 30:09.473
            Get out!

30:09.475 --> 30:10.407
           I'm sorry.

30:11.343 --> 30:12.276
           I'm sorry.

30:13.512 --> 30:14.945
        I'm sorry, uh...

30:14.947 --> 30:16.914
 Please get out before I scream!

30:16.916 --> 30:18.382
  I'm sorry, I just thought...

30:31.096 --> 30:32.029
            You know,

30:32.932 --> 30:35.065
     I've got instincts too.

30:37.136 --> 30:39.903
       You don't love the
     man you're married to.

31:13.205 --> 31:16.006
    Stabber, come over here.

31:16.008 --> 31:17.207
          Jesus Christ.

31:18.143 --> 31:19.877
[Pluto] Tonight's my last night.

31:19.879 --> 31:23.347
     I'm saying sayonara to
     this shit hole manyana.

31:27.620 --> 31:29.286
    You'll be missed, Pluto.

31:29.288 --> 31:32.289
  Hey, what do you say me and
 you hit the town to celebrate?

31:32.291 --> 31:34.391
      I got some moolah...

31:34.393 --> 31:36.960
     They paid me off and it
     ain't even payday yet.

31:38.163 --> 31:39.429
     I don't think so, man.

31:40.366 --> 31:41.999
  Hey the next time you see me,

31:42.001 --> 31:43.934
  you'll be calling me El Jefe.

31:46.272 --> 31:48.672
        Or maybe I'll be
      calling you boss man

31:48.674 --> 31:50.474
         and you'll be
      running these gangs.

31:52.144 --> 31:55.345
     Come on, just a couple
        drinks, Stabber.

31:57.283 --> 31:58.682
           Okay then.

31:58.684 --> 32:00.684
 OK, that's what I like to hear.

32:00.686 --> 32:04.221
     (up tempo violin music)

32:05.557 --> 32:09.960
[Pluto] Don't you think that old
Pluto is gonna forget about you.

32:09.962 --> 32:14.364
    You oughta be Cap's boss
   and I got a toast to make.

32:16.502 --> 32:18.235
      Ladies and gentlemen,

32:19.171 --> 32:20.304
              here

32:20.306 --> 32:23.473
  is the best, damn pipe liner

32:23.475 --> 32:26.677
      in all of West Texas.

32:26.679 --> 32:28.378
    Sit your ass down, Pluto.

32:29.281 --> 32:30.614
       [Pluto] I give you

32:30.616 --> 32:33.717
        the one, the only

32:33.719 --> 32:34.584
             Jim...

32:34.586 --> 32:36.620
        Stabber McNeely.

32:36.622 --> 32:39.022
   ¶ Just a little more love,
     then I'd be dreaming ¶

32:39.024 --> 32:39.690
         (glass breaks)

32:39.692 --> 32:41.558
           (throws up)

32:41.560 --> 32:44.528
      ¶ I could do, yeah ¶

32:46.598 --> 32:49.399
      That's it Jim, you'll
        feel better now.

32:51.170 --> 32:54.371
   You're a bonafide drunkard
   now, welcome to the club.

32:54.373 --> 32:55.572
         [Cap] Move it!

33:07.753 --> 33:11.388
     (anxious violin tones)

33:11.390 --> 33:14.992
     Get up from there, you
  gold-bricking son of a bitch.

33:19.131 --> 33:22.065
 Think you're a little too smart
   to be laying pipe no more?

33:23.168 --> 33:25.235
      You're just asking to
      get your ass run off.

33:29.174 --> 33:31.608
    You need to get the drain
      plate off that tank.

33:31.610 --> 33:33.777
      It ain't bleeding the
   bullshit out of the bottom.

33:34.680 --> 33:36.780
 Maybe that'll wake your ass up.

33:39.385 --> 33:42.652
     (anxious violin tones)

33:59.038 --> 34:01.772
 - That Cap's a son of a bitch.
           - Yes sir.

34:16.355 --> 34:21.425
[Jim] (singing) Florina, Florina

34:22.293 --> 34:26.797
 ¶ Where'd you stay last night ¶

34:27.533 --> 34:32.202
     ¶ Florina, Flori--na! ¶

34:32.838 --> 34:36.840
 ¶ Where'd you go last night? ¶

34:36.842 --> 34:40.844
  ¶ Come home in the morning ¶

34:40.846 --> 34:44.414
   ¶ And the sun don't shine ¶

34:44.416 --> 34:49.319
    ¶ Florina, Floriiinaaa ¶

34:49.321 --> 34:53.223
 ¶ Where'd you stay last night ¶

34:53.225 --> 34:54.424
        [Jim] Florina...

34:54.426 --> 34:57.527
       That swamp gas is
      gettin' to his head.

34:57.529 --> 35:02.299
  It'll kill his ass unless we
   get him outta there quick.

35:02.301 --> 35:06.703
        ¶ Go home in the
      morning and the sun ¶

35:11.877 --> 35:15.145
       (metallic clanking)

35:16.281 --> 35:17.214
              Jim.

35:22.821 --> 35:23.753
              Jim?

35:27.326 --> 35:29.593
           (coughing)

35:35.300 --> 35:37.701
        Get up, you sorry
         son of a bitch.

35:43.809 --> 35:45.242
          Come on, Jim.
        Come on, get him.

35:49.848 --> 35:52.649
         (thuds, grunts)

35:53.852 --> 35:55.919
       [Men] Get him son.
            Come on.

36:01.193 --> 36:02.259
          [Men] Get up.

36:04.863 --> 36:06.930
      Yeah! That a boy Jim.

36:08.333 --> 36:12.269
 (anxious violin, guitar music)

36:13.438 --> 36:15.405
           (men cheer)

36:34.393 --> 36:35.659
           My boy Jim.

36:40.199 --> 36:42.499
       You piece of shit.

36:58.383 --> 37:01.952
  (soft piano and violin music)

37:54.840 --> 37:57.474
       (crickets chirping)

37:57.476 --> 38:00.477
       (soft piano music)

38:24.903 --> 38:25.835
              Hey.

38:28.907 --> 38:30.573
              Say.

38:30.575 --> 38:32.709
 I heard all about what you did.

38:38.317 --> 38:40.750
 You know I'm leaving for good.

38:40.752 --> 38:41.818
           I figured.

38:53.632 --> 38:54.998
        Where you headed?

39:00.005 --> 39:04.874
     (relaxed guitar music)

39:05.944 --> 39:09.446
         (birds singing)

39:25.364 --> 39:27.764
      [Jim] Dent, I did it.

39:27.766 --> 39:29.566
          I married her

39:31.670 --> 39:33.636
and now you and everyone in this

39:33.638 --> 39:37.774
     God-forsaken world can
     call her Lee McNeely.

39:37.776 --> 39:39.542
         How about that?

39:39.544 --> 39:40.977
          (Lee laughs)

39:43.949 --> 39:46.449
      You always asked what
        my money was for.

39:48.053 --> 39:51.755
    Well you'll be content to
  know I found some use for it.

39:52.657 --> 39:54.391
         And who knows?

39:54.393 --> 39:57.894
     Maybe someday I'll need
     some good, cheap labor

39:57.896 --> 40:00.597
      if you happen to know
       anyone interested.

40:05.170 --> 40:06.936
              Well?

40:06.938 --> 40:08.671
    It smells delicious, hon.

40:08.673 --> 40:11.841
       Don't gimme that,
       tell me something.

40:13.044 --> 40:17.147
     We are the sole owners
        of the sorriest,

40:17.149 --> 40:21.084
   oldest oil field servicing
  company in all of West Texas.

40:21.086 --> 40:23.787
         Ooh, I knew it.
     [Jim] Oh calm down now.

40:23.789 --> 40:25.555
       I made a bad deal.

40:25.557 --> 40:27.957
        I bought out Mrs.
      Sullivan on the worst

40:27.959 --> 40:31.060
       layaway plan known
       to man and maybe,

40:31.062 --> 40:35.198
        just maybe, if I
      work 18 hours a day,

40:35.200 --> 40:37.934
        seven days a week
      and give up breakfast

40:37.936 --> 40:41.938
   and chewing gum and picture
   shows and I get an amazing

40:41.940 --> 40:45.041
  string of luck, we might just
  be able to make the payments.

40:45.043 --> 40:46.643
          I don't care.

40:46.645 --> 40:48.978
    You will care when we're
    eating beans every night.

40:50.048 --> 40:53.049
          I love beans.
            [Jim] Oh!

40:53.051 --> 40:55.819
           (laughing)

40:55.821 --> 40:59.722
  (upbeat country guitar music)

41:17.576 --> 41:19.943
     You know, the surefire
       way to get through

41:19.945 --> 41:22.812
     to an old timer is to
     get down on his level.

41:22.814 --> 41:26.015
        Make him laugh.
     I know what I'm doing.

41:26.017 --> 41:29.519
  I know you do, big boss man.

41:30.121 --> 41:31.054
            Shut up.

41:43.702 --> 41:44.701
           Mr. Coker?

42:00.185 --> 42:02.118
     My name's Jim McNeely.

42:05.824 --> 42:09.592
That road you just come on in on

42:09.594 --> 42:12.762
       don't lead nowhere
        but right here.

42:12.764 --> 42:15.532
      Mr. Coker, I heard it
       said in Odessa that

42:15.534 --> 42:18.034
      you'd shoot the next
      fella that came out

42:18.036 --> 42:20.737
       here asking about
    leasing the Coker ranch.

42:21.940 --> 42:24.641
  I ain't a lease broker and I

42:24.643 --> 42:26.676
       damn sure don't aim
      to get shot, neither.

42:26.678 --> 42:29.178
     What in the confounded
       hell do you want?

42:29.180 --> 42:31.881
        Not a damn thing
        sir, unless you'd

42:33.218 --> 42:35.885
     spare a little of that
   Beechnut you're chewin' on.

42:46.831 --> 42:50.199
 They say you're a fool 'cause
 you refuse to lease your land.

42:50.201 --> 42:52.869
        You'd rather let
        'em rob you blind

42:52.871 --> 42:54.837
         than get what's
        rightfully yours.

43:01.146 --> 43:02.979
    Shit with what they say.

43:02.981 --> 43:06.349
     I don't agree with 'em
     or I wouldn't be here.

43:06.351 --> 43:09.619
    I just think you haven't
  been offered a fair deal yet.

43:10.689 --> 43:14.757
     You need a partner who
    can help you get the oil

43:15.760 --> 43:17.894
    out of the ground before
       they suck you dry.

43:28.607 --> 43:31.307
        (Coker laughing)

43:32.277 --> 43:34.243
    You're the worst goddamn

43:34.245 --> 43:36.946
        tobacco chewer I
      ever seen in my life.

43:36.948 --> 43:38.147
 I never claimed to be an expert

43:38.149 --> 43:39.949
       in chewing tobacco
       or anything else.

43:41.953 --> 43:43.886
       I'm just a poor boy
        trying to get by.

43:52.764 --> 43:56.933
(mid tempo country guitar music)

44:28.400 --> 44:31.668
        (metal clanking)

44:34.239 --> 44:37.040
         (bird chirping)

44:43.782 --> 44:45.048
       Take a look at it.

44:46.351 --> 44:48.918
         [Jim] Driller!
 Let's test this son of a bitch.

44:57.862 --> 44:59.829
            Goddamn.

44:59.831 --> 45:02.331
 Driller, give me two more feet.

45:17.882 --> 45:20.183
           (cheering)

45:26.758 --> 45:29.459
 [Barry] You did it, you did it.

45:32.764 --> 45:34.497
     [Jim] We're in the oil
      business now, sugar.

45:44.876 --> 45:47.176
          [Jim] Barry.
          What is this?

45:48.246 --> 45:50.413
    That's your 1% interest.

45:52.016 --> 45:55.151
      But Jim, I'm happy to
       help an old friend.

45:55.420 --> 45:57.320
         Hell with that.

45:57.322 --> 45:59.355
   I wouldn't have even known
  about this deal without you.

46:00.925 --> 46:01.991
         Thank you, Jim.

46:02.227 --> 46:06.362
     (relaxed violin music)

46:33.224 --> 46:38.094
     So you're telling me,
  you got no geological stats,

46:38.096 --> 46:43.166
  no geophysics, nothing but a
 lot of hot air and high hopes?

46:43.401 --> 46:45.134
     And cheap leases, sir.

46:45.403 --> 46:48.104
  $6 an acre, can't beat that.

46:49.440 --> 46:51.207
           Not a uh...

46:51.209 --> 46:54.210
    deal for the risk-averse,
        that's for sure.

46:56.381 --> 47:00.316
     Not exactly my idea of
   aggressive expansion, Dent.

47:00.318 --> 47:05.254
   Well I'm no geologist and
Scurry County's not oil country.

47:05.256 --> 47:08.257
      However, it's a shit
       load of cheap land

47:08.259 --> 47:10.259
          in West Texas
      without a hole in it.

47:11.262 --> 47:12.395
    I'm willing to give y'all

47:12.397 --> 47:15.031
     until tomorrow morning
        to consider it.

47:16.534 --> 47:20.336
    Otherwise I'm just gonna
    shop it on down the road.

47:30.615 --> 47:35.351
        (relaxed country
      guitar, violin music)

48:28.406 --> 48:30.673
    Santa Rita, gimme a sign.

48:48.426 --> 48:52.428
 (relaxed violin, guitar music)

48:56.701 --> 48:57.600
            Hot damn.

49:00.405 --> 49:01.304
            Hot damn.

49:09.147 --> 49:11.080
       To bet it all on a
       stupid horseshoe?

49:12.550 --> 49:13.482
           Goddammit.

49:19.557 --> 49:21.691
     Well, how did it look?

49:21.693 --> 49:23.960
       Hmm, like you said.

49:25.063 --> 49:26.529
  Cheap lease is for a reason.

49:28.032 --> 49:32.568
   You know I was thinking we
  could redo the guest bedroom.

49:33.705 --> 49:35.304
           Redo what?

49:35.306 --> 49:37.173
   We already got a bed and a
   dresser in there already.

49:38.309 --> 49:39.475
      What else do we need?

49:39.477 --> 49:41.510
       We haven't even had
       a guest over once.

49:42.380 --> 49:45.114
I don't know, maybe a kids room.

49:48.453 --> 49:50.152
            You know,

49:50.154 --> 49:51.087
            someday.

49:58.563 --> 50:00.229
              Hon,

50:00.231 --> 50:01.630
         we barely have
       time for you and I.

50:01.632 --> 50:04.000
       How the hell are we
    gonna have time for kids?

50:04.002 --> 50:06.502
      We make time, that's
         how it's done.

50:06.504 --> 50:10.106
      It won't be easy but
       I will have a son

50:10.108 --> 50:13.609
  so I can teach him how to be
  a real cowboy, work the land.

50:16.080 --> 50:16.746
     Cowboy huh, cowboy huh?

50:16.748 --> 50:17.680
            (laughs)

50:18.649 --> 50:19.582
         You want a son?

